body:
David Tennant

Guys I’m supposed be going to Megacon in May and meeting David Tennant! I’m freaking out! Like I’ve looked up to this man forever! He is the freaking doctor! Not even mentioning his other roles as Barty Crouch Jr. in Harry Potter GoF or in HTTYD as Spitelout. I’m just having a total freak out! And I have no idea what I want to have signed because I have tons of things he could sign. I also don’t even know if I’m going to be able to talk, like it’s David Tennant how do you even talk to him? 😅😂

summary:
Behind the Scenes of New Earth (Part Six) 

Excerpts from Benjamin Cook’s article in Doctor Who Magazine #369 

 DWM: Does David...
caption:
Behind the Scenes of New Earth (Part Six)

Excerpts from Benjamin Cook’s article in Doctor Who Magazine #369

DWM: Does David ever feel ridiculous on Doctor Who?

David: “Well, it’s all ever so slightly silly, isn’t it?” he laughs when we catch up a few months later. “It’s a story about a man who travels through the universe in a phone box, so you can’t really allow yourself to enter the realms of self-consciousness, or I think the whole thing would fall apart. You have to sell it with absolute conviction, and completely believe in these moments that you’re in. Showers in elevators are all very well, but it’s most difficult when you’re acting against elements that aren’t there - green screen being the obvious one. You enter into the world of it when you take the job on, I think. Everyone here knows why we’re doing it, and what we’re doing it for, so it’s not like anyone’s pointing and laughing! It’s a very understanding crew.

DWM: Are you a cat person?

David: Erm, not particularly. I’m not big on animals much. I don’t mind cats, I don’t mind dogs, but I’m not a great lover of either. I don’t get squishy at the thought of them like some people do. I quite like the coolness of cats. I like the ‘sod you’ quality that a cat has - you can shower it in love and it’ll just wander off. Dogs are transparent; I suppose that’s what makes them lovable. But I like the enigma of cats.
